{
  "stanzas": [
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "number": 1,
          "text": "The dawn of God’s dear Sabbath"
        },
        {
          "number": 2,
          "text": "Breaks o’er the earth again,"
        },
        {
          "number": 3,
          "text": "As some sweet summer morning"
        },
        {
          "number": 4,
          "text": "After a night of pain;"
        },
        {
          "number": 5,
          "text": "It comes as cooling showers"
        },
        {
          "number": 6,
          "text": "To some exhausted land,"
        },
        {
          "number": 7,
          "text": "As shade of clustered palm trees"
        },
        {
          "number": 8,
          "text": "‘Mid weary wastes of sand."
        }
      ],
      "number": 1
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "number": 1,
          "text": "Lord, we would bring for offering,"
        },
        {
          "number": 2,
          "text": "Though marred with earthly soil,"
        },
        {
          "number": 3,
          "text": "A week of earnest labor,"
        },
        {
          "number": 4,
          "text": "Of steady, faithful toil,"
        },
        {
          "number": 5,
          "text": "Fair fruits of self denial,"
        },
        {
          "number": 6,
          "text": "Of strong, deep love to Thee,"
        },
        {
          "number": 7,
          "text": "Fostered by Thine own Spirit,"
        },
        {
          "number": 8,
          "text": "In true humility."
        }
      ],
      "number": 2
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "number": 1,
          "text": "And we would bring our burden"
        },
        {
          "number": 2,
          "text": "Of sinful thought and deed,"
        },
        {
          "number": 3,
          "text": "In Thy pure presence kneeling,"
        },
        {
          "number": 4,
          "text": "From bondage to be freed,"
        },
        {
          "number": 5,
          "text": "Our heart’s most bitter sorrow"
        },
        {
          "number": 6,
          "text": "For all Thy work undone-"
        },
        {
          "number": 7,
          "text": "So many talents wasted!"
        },
        {
          "number": 8,
          "text": "So few bright laurels won!"
        }
      ],
      "number": 3
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "number": 1,
          "text": "And with that sorrow mingling,"
        },
        {
          "number": 2,
          "text": "A steadfast faith, and sure,"
        },
        {
          "number": 3,
          "text": "And love so deep and fervent,"
        },
        {
          "number": 4,
          "text": "For Thee to make it pure,"
        },
        {
          "number": 5,
          "text": "In Thy dear presence finding"
        },
        {
          "number": 6,
          "text": "The pardon that we need,"
        },
        {
          "number": 7,
          "text": "And then the peace so lasting-"
        },
        {
          "number": 8,
          "text": "Celestial peace indeed."
        }
      ],
      "number": 4
    }
  ],
  "title": "The Dawn of God's Dear Sabbath"
}
